  <p>Unrecognized commands get generic compression: ANSI stripping, empty line removal, and long output truncation.</p>

  <h2>23 Auto-Rewritten Aliases</h2>
  <p>After <code>lean-ctx init --global</code>, these commands are transparently compressed:</p>
  <pre><code>git, npm, pnpm, yarn, cargo, docker, docker-compose, kubectl, k,
gh, pip, pip3, ruff, go, golangci-lint, eslint, prettier, tsc,
ls, find, grep, curl, wget</code></pre>

  <h2>Persistent Stats</h2>
  <p>
    LeanCTX tracks savings persistently in <code>~/.lean-ctx/stats.json</code>.
    Every MCP session and shell hook invocation contributes to the cumulative stats.
    Use <code>lean-ctx gain</code> to view in the terminal, or <code>lean-ctx dashboard</code>
    for the web UI at localhost:3333.
  </p>

  <h2>Exit Codes</h2>
  <p>
    In shell hook mode (<code>-c</code>), LeanCTX forwards the exit code of the wrapped command.
    This ensures scripts and CI pipelines work correctly. If the command fails (non-zero exit),
    the full original output is saved to <code>~/.lean-ctx/tee/</code> for debugging.
  </p>
